Sometime overnight between Friday and Saturday, I took a trip into the Twilight Zone. It lasted until this evening, but I know I was awake because I attended some terrific sessions with Wordcamp KC. It felt like an parallel universe ... and it was awesome!

So, what do I mean I went into the Twilight Zone?

[caption id="attachment_423" align="aligncenter" width="300"]<img class="wp-image-423 size-medium" src="http://livinginalphabetsoup.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Twilight_Zone_Optical.svg_-2-300x300.png" alt="Twilight_Zone_Optical.svg" width="300" height="300" /> <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File%3ATwilight_Zone_Optical.svg">Source: By SunOfErat (Own work) [CC0], via Wikimedia Commons</a>[/caption]<a name="more"></a>Friday night was an ordinary night with plenty of meltdowns to go around. Child started the evening by having a meltdown because he didn't have enough <a href="http://www.tbonesbaseball.com/" target="_blank">T-Bones</a> bucks to get dinner &amp; a drink AND dessert ... but the little girls did. *mind you, both of the older children were informed they could get the simple hot dog combo and didn't want to* Then after that meltdown, he immediately went into another meltdown because someone else sat in his seat. This was followed by a different child suddenly having a meltdown because the stick came out of her cotton candy, rendering it inedible. Apparently. Who knew? We finally got most everyone settled and happily eating when they decided to go play at the playground. I have NO idea what happened but we ended up with a massive meltdown up there within minutes so hubby left to go deal with that ... leaving me in my seat eating my son's nachos ... watching baseball and trying to remember why in the world we planned a family outing in the first place! Yet, they do take some really cute photos. *laugh*

